<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-13T11:43:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-13T11:43:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8494</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-13T16:00:00-00:43">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 14, 6.18
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Legation informed yesterday that at the request of Government of Germany
                            the Spanish Government has instructed its representative here to
                            transmit to the Liberian Government a declaration by Germany announcing
                            among other things that from January 11, 1918, waters of entire Liberian
                            coast are in zone of submarine activity.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BRC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>